  "texts": [
    "Following Luecken et al.",
    "43, the overall score y is the sum of the averaged batch correction metric y batch weighted by 0.4 and the averaged biological conservation metric y bio weighted by 0.6,y batch 𝒩 (y iLISI ω + y gc ω + y kBET ω)/3 y bio 𝒩 (y NMI ω + y ARI ω + y ilF1 ω + y cLISI ω)/4 y 𝒩 0.4 ⋅ y batch + 0.6 ⋅ y bio(35)where ω = embed for embedding or graph outputs, and ω = feat for feature outputs.scMIB.",
    "As an extension of scIB, the scMIB overall score y is computed from the batch correction, modality alignment and biological conservation metrics defined on both the embedding and feature space.",
